SystemThe wrecked vehicle. Photo: supplied Multimedia &nbsp; &nbsp; User Galleries &nbsp; &nbsp; News in Pictures Send us your pictures &nbsp; &nbsp; Send us your stories THREE workers were injured in an accident along the N2 at the Amanzimtoti River on Friday at around 1.30am. Reports from the scene indicate that the men were travelling from the Eastern Cape when the vehicle veered off the highway, plunged down an embankment, its wreckage coming to rest on the banks of the Amanzimtoti River.Netcare 911 media liaison officer Chris Botha, paramedics and SAPS found the vehicle on its side. The occupants managed to clamber from the wreckage and were found on the grass behind the town hall. After medics stabilised the injured they were transported to hospital. - Supplied24.com encourages commentary submitted via MyNews24. Contributions of 200 words or more will be considered for publication.